Instructions: Beginning Wednesday, April 15th, individuals over the age of five AND who have symptoms will be registered for drive-through testing. To find out if you should be tested call the WhidbeyHealth Coronavirus Hotline at 360-240-4055 during noted hours. At the drive-up facility, the medical team will take a sample nasal swab, which will then be sent to one of the approved off-island testing laboratories. Turn-around times for test results are reliably less than 24 hours; often sooner.
comments:
If you are symptomatic, you may be eligible for testing at WhidbeyHealth Medical Center.
How do you know when to call? In the past 48 hours have you had any of the following symptoms?:

Fever (>100 F) or possible fever symptoms/alternating shivering and sweating
New cough
New shortness of breath or trouble breathing, severe wheezing
New muscle aches
New fatigue or tiredness
Sore throat
Diarrhea
New loss of smell or taste/or change in taste
If you've been exposed to COVID-19

Instructions: Visit www.scheduletest.com to request a test and schedule a pick up at your local pharmacy or have it delivered directly to your home. Payment is due upon pick up or prior to delivery. Once ready, you will receive your results through your preferred method of communication, email or text.  Your pharmacist will be available for questions.
comments: Skip the long lines at testing drive-thurs and get testing in the comfort of your own home with an at-home saliva PCR test for COVID-19.  Currently insurance is unable to be billed, cost of the test is $139.99 + applicable delivery fees if delivery method is selected.  Sample collection can not occur on Fridays or Saturdays.  People who are experiencing symptoms cannot pick up their tests. They can either send someone without symptoms to pick up their test or have it delivered.
